{"id": "1450623504616657089", "channel_id": "1450623504616657089", "type": 0, "author_id": "939547142090018816", "author_name": "snorlax01", "author_bot": false, "content": "Will Silver Prime purchases be at one point converted to the national price value of each individual country? For example, in countries with a weaker dollar, the cost of 5 USD in their currency can equate to roughly 3 meals in their currency. Take Vietnam for instance, for every 1 USD it will be equivalent to 26k Vietnamese Dong; which can then be used to pay for street food such as pho, banh mi and spring rolls for as little as 20k Vietnamese Dong each. Then compare that to mid to high value paid packs such as the recent Silver Frost Archives pack valued at 980 Silver Prime (or 15 USD) or the Dawnbringer's Guidance valued at 3280 Silver Prime (or 50 USD.) While players like them can simply choose not to pay for the Silver Prime in USD using their national currency, they will miss out alot on many mid to high value paid packs in the coming future.", "timestamp": "2025-12-16T22:59:54.782000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 4}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1450623504616657089", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Purchasing Silver Prime", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785"]}
